The paper discusses object-oriented programming concepts and verification problems, which are typically studied in the software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new rule for information hiding, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper addresses the problem of reference leaks, which is related to memory management and falls under the category of operating systems (cs.OH). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to solving class invariants without introducing new language constructs or programmer annotations, which could be considered a contribution to the emerging technologies (cs.ET) sub-category.
